@Node Intr "FreshMDL : Introduction"

  @{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

    I created @{fg highlight}FreshMDL@{fg text} because I was really tired of @{b}MakeDefLibs@{ub} and @{b}LibMan@{ub}, tired to
    join  ALL  the  drawers everytime I wanted to test one of my own set of commands.
    Moreover @{b}MakeDefLibs@{ub} is so slow and big...

    So I made @{fg highlight}FreshMDL@{fg text}.

    @{fg highlight}FreshMDL@{fg text} uses temporary files in each drawer found in  @{i}BlitzLibs:@{ui}.  So  when  you
    want  to  create the @{i}DefLibs@{ui} @{fg highlight}FreshMDL@{fg text} joins all those files and not all the libs.
    Updating @{i}DefLibs @{ui}is really simple and fast.

    @{fg highlight}FreshMDL@{fg text} recognise executable files, so you can leave sources of your libs in the
    drawers.  @{fg highlight}FreshMDL@{fg text}  is  also  very  small,  only  8  Ko comparing to the 12 Ko of
    @{b}MakeDefLibs@{ub} or the 34 Ko of @{b}LibMan@{ub}.

  @{b}@{u}See also@{ub}@{uu}

    @{" FreshMDL : Intallation    " link Inst}
    @{" FreshMDL : Using FreshMDL " link Usin}
@EndNode
