@Node Usin "FreshMDL : Using FreshMDL"

  @{b}@{u}Using FreshMDL@{ub}@{uu}

    @{b}First use@{ub}
    When you use it for the first time @{fg highlight}FreshMDL@{fg text} creates  a  temporary  file  in  each
    drawer.  These temporaty files (@{i}.libs.tmp@{ui}) will be used to create @{i}DefLibs@{ui}. Once a
    temporary file is created it is added to the @{i}DefLibs@{ui} file.

    @{b}Updating@{ub}
    To update a @{i}.libs.tmp@{ui} you can either delete it (then  it  will  be  made  calling
    @{fg highlight}FreshMDL@{fg text}) or CD to the directory that you want to update and enter :

      @{i}@{bg text}@{fg shine}BlitzLibs:MyLibs>@{bg background}@{fg text} @{ui}FreshMDL dir

    You can also gives the name of the directory you want to update :

      @{i}@{bg text}@{fg shine}Sys3.0:>@{bg background}@{fg text} @{ui}FreshMDL MyLibs

    To update all @{i}.libs.tmp@{ui} and also update your @{i}DefLibs@{ui} enter :

      @{i}@{bg text}@{fg shine}Sys3.0:>@{bg background}@{fg text} @{ui}FreshMDL all

    To only update @{i}DefLibs@{ui} enter :

      @{i}@{bg text}@{fg shine}Sys3.0:>@{bg background}@{fg text} @{ui}FreshMDL
@EndNode
